# Prefer Private Readonly Fields

When a member is private, only assigned at construction, and never needs property semantics (binding, serialization, interface contract), use a `private readonly` field instead of a get-only auto-property.

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — private get-only auto-property with no reason to be a property
private PipelineDescriptor Descriptor { get; }
private ComponentTypeRegistry TypeRegistry { get; } = new();

// ✅ GOOD — private readonly field
private readonly PipelineDescriptor _descriptor;
private readonly ComponentTypeRegistry _typeRegistry = new();
```

Properties are appropriate when:
- The member is part of a public/internal API surface
- It implements an interface or is an override
- It needs data-binding, serialization, or configuration binding
- It has a non-trivial getter or setter
